The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | HCL to buy Dubai firm
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      HCL to buy Dubai firm
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, July 8: HCL Infosystems Ltd has agreed to acquire a 60 per cent stake in Dubai-based technology services firm NTS Group for about $6.5 million.         
	According to a statement to the bourses, the acquisition will help HCL Infosystems gain access to West Asia and Africa to address system and service integration needs in the regions.        
	NTS has over 100 technology and support employees in the UAE.         
	It offers solutions in hardware, enterprise software, infrastructure and networking, e-security and web development.         
	This acquisition will see NTSs customers across West Asia get access to HCL Infosystems three decades of expertise in the space. It will help us to accelerate growth in our targeted international markets, offering a complete set of products, services and solutions. Ajai Chowdhry, chairman and CEO of HCL Infosystems, said.        
	HCL Infosystems and NTS will now focus on building their business.         
	Shares of HCL Infosystems dropped 25 paise to settle at Rs 112.90 on the Bombay Stock Exchange today.                                                                                                                                      
